More than 200 surveys and more than 30 searches were conducted.
It is suspected that Sh. Gustav received more than 8 thousand. a bribe of euros, G. Steponavičius - 15 thousand. euros, V. Gapšys - more than 27 thousand. E. Masiulis is suspected of taking more than 106 thousand. euro bribe.
The Labour Party is suspected of bribery and influence trading, the Liberal Movement is suspected of bribery, influence trading and abuse, and MG Baltic is suspected of bribery and influence trading of these parties.
It is suspected that the politicians consulted with R. Kurlianskis, vice-president of the MG Baltic concern, about bribes, and later proposed or supported initiatives favorable to the concern in the Seimas or other institutions.
