Scientists argue that it is also necessary to talk about the fact that the desire of people to know wildlife can sometimes be harmful.
"It's obvious to me that the bears were very frightened by the drone.
From their movements it can be seen that they are panicking.
If a drone didn't fly around, they probably would have chosen a safer path or overcome it more slowly or more cautiously.
