In the southwest of the U.S. state of Texas, a newlywed couple who had married just a few hours earlier were killed in a helicopter crash.
William Troy Byler, 24, and his co-wife, Bailee Raye Ackerman Byler, were killed Sunday shortly after midnight when a helicopter slammed into a hill 16 km northwest of Juwaldi and 129 km west of San Antonio, local peace judge Steven Kennedy said.
