"It's a very rocky area of uneven terrain, and that hill is about 120-150 meters high," Mr Kennedy said.
G. D. Lawrence piloted the aircraft of that family for many years.
According to Mr Kennedy, he also piloted helicopters while serving in Vietnam.
After the autopsy, it should become clear what the physical condition of the pilot was and whether it could not become the cause of the disaster.
The helicopter crashed about 5-10 minutes after takeoff.
His wreckage glowed in a wide radius on a rocky hillside, while the hull remained "dangerously suspended," flight safety investigator Craig Hatch of the National Transportation Security Board (NTSB) said during a press conference on Monday.
Investigators intend to take out the wreckage and then inspect it thoroughly, but it won't be easy for the tow truck and truck to reach the area, he said.
